Thulani Gqirana, News24ER24 (Picture: Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; A woman was airlifted off the Paarl Rock Mountain after she injured her leg while hiking, paramedics said on Sunday.The woman fell and sustained a serious injury to her lower leg, ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said. The woman, in the 30s, was treated on scene before she was airlifted to Mediclinic in Stellenbosch for further treatment. The woman was with her husband and two children, who were returned to the bottom of the mountain. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.